Cortex XSOAR Analytics App for Splunk

Version: 1.3.2
App Folder Name: cortex-xsoar-analytics

Overview:
========
The Cortex XSOAR Analytics Add-On for Splunk enables automatic ingestion of incidents from Cortex XSOAR into Splunk, specifically designed to enhance real-time reporting capabilities. It allows the creation of customizable dashboards and detailed reports, providing greater visibility into incident trends and metrics. This integration helps security teams manage incidents efficiently and make informed decisions based on comprehensive, up-to-date data.

Requirements:
=============
- Tested for Splunk version 9 and newer
- Network access to XSOAR web/API port

Installation Instructions:
==========================
Single Search Head:
1. Install the app on the Search Head.
2. Use the setup page guideline to add the necessary credentials and server URLs (SOAR URL, SOAR API KEY, Splunk API key).
3. Restart Splunk.

Search Head Cluster:
1. Install the app on the Deployer.
2. Deploy the app to the Search Head Cluster.
3. Login to one of the search heads and use the setup page guideline to add the necessary credentials and server URLs (SOAR URL, SOAR API KEY, Splunk API key).
4. Copy the ./local directory to the Deployer.
5. Deploy the app to the Search Head Cluster.

Configuration Instructions:
===========================
Use the setup page guideline to add the necessary credentials and server URLs (SOAR URL, SOAR API KEY, Splunk API key).

To Change Credentials:

Single Search Head:
1. Remove password.conf and system-token.conf from $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/cortex-xsoar-analytics/local.
2. Modify the app.conf stanza in $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/cortex-xsoar-analytics/local as follows:
   [install]
   is_configured = false
3. Use the setup page guideline to add the necessary credentials and server URLs (SOAR URL, SOAR API KEY, Splunk API key).
4. Restart Splunk.

Search Head Cluster:
1. Remove the $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/cortex-xsoar-analytics/local folder.
2. Use the setup page guideline to add the necessary credentials and server URLs (SOAR URL, SOAR API KEY, Splunk API key).
3. Restart Splunk.
4. Deploy the app to the Search Head Cluster.

Usage Instructions:
===================
SPL Command:
| xsoarsearch --created_earliest <string> --created_latest <string> --modified_earliest <string> --modified_latest <string> --query <string> --exclude_fields <string>

Description:
Command allows you to search for incidents in Cortex XSOAR directly from Splunk.\
              created_earliest -> Earliest creation time. Default: 24 hours.\
              created_latest -> Latest creation time. Default: 0 seconds.\
              modified_earliest -> Earliest modified time (Relative time is converted in UTC for SOAR Query).\
              modified_latest -> Latest modified time (Relative time is converted in UTC for SOAR Query).\
              query -> Cortex XSOAR query.  If it's not specified, it will be by default ''.\
              exclude_fields -> Fields to be excluded from output, in comma separated form. Labels will be always excluded.

Example:
| xsoarsearch --created_earliest 360day --created_latest 5min --modified_earliest 24h --modified_latest 1s --query status:Active --exclude_fields "labels,incidentduration"

Comment:
--exclude_fields by default will exclude "labels".

Splunk Macro:
=============
Macro Name: xsoar_incidents(1)

Arguments:
1. modified_earliest

Definition:
xsoarsearch --created_earliest 360d --modified_earliest $modified_earliest$

Evaluation:
iseval = 0

Dashboard:
==========
The dashboard replicates the default Cortex XSOAR Incident Dashboard and is designed to provide a baseline and a starting point for further per-customer requirements.

Known Issues and Limitations:
=============================
- This integration will pull all the configured non-empty Cortex XSOAR fields as per the selected time range.
- Incident labels will not be extracted from the incident context.

Troubleshooting Tips:
=====================
- Execute "xsoarsearch" and check the results and search logs. In most cases, the error and instructions should appear as a search result. In case of any unexpected errors, please share the Job Inspector logs with the support team.
- Verify network connectivity between Splunk and the XSOAR instance.
- Ensure that the provided API keys have the necessary permissions to access the XSOAR incidents.

Helpful Information:
====================
